template:
You are a language expert skilled in text structure analysis. Your task is to semantically and logically split a longer narrative text.

## I. Task Description
- You will receive a longer text segment (e.g., novel paragraphs, narrative passages, etc.);
- Please identify semantic or plot breakpoints and divide it into no more than `{max_segments}` natural paragraphs (the fewer the better);
- Each paragraph should be as semantically complete as possible, such as progression of time, event transitions, changes in character relationships, shifts in narrative focus, etc.;
- **The last paragraph can be an incomplete fragment, used for concatenation with subsequent text.**

## II. Output Format
Please output in strict JSON format, as follows:
```json
{
  "segments": [
    "First semantically complete paragraph (length no less than {min_length} characters)",
    "(Optional) Second semantically complete paragraph (length no less than {min_length} characters)",
...,
    "Last paragraph (can be a fragment or empty string, no character limit)"
  ]
}
```

## III. Additional Requirements
- If it cannot be naturally split into multiple paragraphs, you can return only one complete paragraph and set the others as empty strings;
- Please do not add any explanations, comments, or formatting tags other than JSON;
- All paragraph content must be strings to ensure JSON parsing.

## IV. Text to be Processed
Please split the following text segment:
```
{text}
```
